            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once starting to brown, add the <strong>carrot batons </strong>and <strong>chopped pepper </strong>to the pan with the <strong>grated ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil </strong>and cook for a further 3-4 min or until fragrant and starting to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>gochujang paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>soy sauce </strong>in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[510ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>spiced stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1672754305289-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
